<h2>Riding Styles</h2>

<h3>Freeride Foil (Primary)</h3>
<p>Windswell gliding and small-to-medium groundswell. Emphasis on efficiency, glide, and bump riding. Uses the NF Pro 4'2" board with all equipment pairings above.</p>

<h3>Wave Foil (Big Swell)</h3>
<p>Overhead+ groundswell (10+ second period, 1.5m+ face height). Requires the 3'10" 8L duck-dive board. <strong>Equipment matrix for wave conditions: coming soon.</strong></p>

<div class="not-prose p-4 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-950/30 border border-red-200 dark:border-red-900/50 shadow-card rounded-lg mt-4">
  <p class="text-red-700 dark:text-red-400 text-sm"><strong>⚠️ Board selection in big swell is safety-critical.</strong> The 19L freeride board cannot be duck-dived under overhead breaking waves. Riding it in big surf risks injury and equipment damage. The forecast system flags when groundswell conditions require the wave board.</p>
